The paper deals with algorithms for lattice problems, which are typically studied in the subfield of computer science known as computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which are studied in the subfield of computer science known as numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) in the sense that it deals with the problem of finding the shortest vector in a lattice, which is related to the problem of coding theory. Finally, the paper involves machine learning (cs.LG) in the sense that it uses a convex programming formulation to approximate an M-ellipsoid, which is a technique that is commonly used in machine learning.
